221
00:18:42,160 --> 00:18:46,800
We talked about this earlier, Lenny, creative 
destruction is this economic concept that sits  

222
00:18:46,800 --> 00:18:52,800
at the heart of capitalism. Creative destruction 
basically says, "Under capitalism, it's dynamic.  

223
00:18:52,800 --> 00:18:58,240
New products and services displace or disrupt old 
products and services, companies and methods."  

224
00:18:59,160 --> 00:19:04,040
It's why our economy has grown sixfold over the 
last a hundred years. It's remarkable. It's why  

225
00:19:04,040 --> 00:19:09,680
we have this amazing multi-trillion dollar 
economy. But it comes with some negative  

226
00:19:09,680 --> 00:19:14,960
unintended consequences, which is that people 
both in jobs and out of jobs, they're anxious and  

227
00:19:14,960 --> 00:19:22,400
fearful. There's no program that addresses that.
That's what we're going after here. We're trying  

228
00:19:22,400 --> 00:19:28,720
to be the solve for the unintended consequences 
of the thing that is so positive in many ways  

229
00:19:29,320 --> 00:19:32,960
and that we as product people love because 
we get to build new products and displace  

230
00:19:32,960 --> 00:19:38,720
old products. I'll just say one more thing. 
The reason you know this creative destruction  

231
00:19:38,720 --> 00:19:43,720
works so well is if you compare our economy 
to the late Soviet Union's economy. They  

232
00:19:43,720 --> 00:19:48,440
were a planned economy with no creative 
destruction. So there was no innovation,  

233
00:19:48,440 --> 00:19:53,680
and eventually it just failed. It 
just collapsed. It's remarkable,  

234
00:19:53,680 --> 00:19:58,760
this is a huge country with a massive military 
