recruiters who are willing to, in a protected 
way, do a couple of conversations a month,  

336
00:28:46,080 --> 00:28:50,200
helping people think about their candidate 
market fit. And if anyone listening to the  

337
00:28:50,200 --> 00:28:55,920
show is a recruiter, please come join us and 
volunteer. We need more recruiters. I know  

338
00:28:55,920 --> 00:29:01,080
many of you want to give back and you don't know 
how. You tell me this. Here's a way to give it.

339
00:29:01,080 --> 00:29:09,000
Mm-hmm. Love that. Okay, and so the intent of this 
is that you're trying to figure out, one, what  

340
00:29:09,000 --> 00:29:16,560
does the market want, and how do I be honest about 
what it wants because what you want may not exist  

341
00:29:16,560 --> 00:29:21,040
right now, and then, two, help you refine your 
pitch and how you're approaching and who you're  

342
00:29:21,040 --> 00:29:24,720
talking to. Is there anything else that comes out 
of doing this exercise? Because I think people  

343
00:29:24,720 --> 00:29:28,400
might be hearing this, like, "Ah, so much work. 
I have enough work to do, all these interviews.  

344
00:29:28,400 --> 00:29:32,480
Got to reach out to people. I got kids and 
a family. I have to write this two-pager  

345
00:29:32,480 --> 00:29:36,960
now and listening tour." What other benefits 
